<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,577,1144]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
REMARKS.—This is the smallest of the Ecuadorian species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1905" box="[823,946,578,603]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Majeorona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[823,946,578,603]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Majeorona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a body length about 
<quantity box="[1232,1310,577,604]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="28.0">28 mm</quantity>
and a wing span of less than 
<quantity box="[346,428,613,640]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="80.0">80 mm</quantity>
. The green head and thorax are marked with and the abdomen is piceous, the postclypeus does not extend anteriorly beyond the supra-antennal plates when viewed from the dorsal side, and the lack of infuscation on the fore wing radial and radiomedial crossveins easily distinguish it from the remaining Ecuadorian 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1905" box="[151,274,722,747]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Majeorona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,274,722,747]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Majeorona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
